enum eNktDboClass

Represents the INktDbObject classes. INktParam implementors also make use of this Enum, since they wrap an INktDbObject implementor internally.

Enumerator
clsNull 

Null class.
This is the class for INktDbObject implementors returned by an unsuccessful query to the DB. This value should not be returned by an INktParam unless it is the result of an invalid cast.

clsFundamental 

Fundamental class.
INktParam implementors in this class represent basic types (i.e. int, bool, int64, etc).

clsStruct 

Struct class.

clsUnion 

Union class.

clsArray 

Array class.

clsPointer 

Pointer class.

clsReference 

Reference class.

clsEnumeration 

Enumeration class.
INktDbObject implementors in this class represent a whole Enum type, while INktParam implementors represent a sole member of a given Enum type.

clsFunction 

Function class.
This member is not valid for INktParam implementors.

clsFunctionType 

FunctionType class.

clsClassConstructor 

ClassConstructor class.
INktDbObject implementors in this class represent class constructor functions.

clsClassDestructor 

ClassDestructor class.
INktDbObject implementors in this class represent class destructor functions.

clsClassOperatorMethod 

ClassOperatorMethod class.
INktDbObject implementors in this class represent class operator functions.

clsClassMethod 

ClassMethod class.
INktDbObject implementors in this class represent class method functions.

clsClassConverter 

ClassConverter class.
INktDbObject implementors in this class represent class converter functions.

enum eNktDboFunctionFlags

enum eNktDboFundamentalType

Represents C++ fundamental types. Equivalencies for C# can be found here.

Enumerator
ftNone 

Does not represent any type.
This is the type for INktDbObject implementors which do not belong to any basic type or were invalidly cast.

ftSignedByte 

Represents the signed char C++ fundamental type. Its equivalent in C# is sbyte.

ftUnsignedByte 

Represents the unsigned char C++ fundamental type. Its equivalent in C# is byte.

ftSignedWord 

Represents the signed short C++ fundamental type. Its equivalents in C# are short and char.

ftUnsignedWord 

Represents the unsigned short C++ fundamental type. Its equivalent in C# is ushort.

ftSignedDoubleWord 

Represents the signed int C++ fundamental type. Its equivalent in C# is int.

ftUnsignedDoubleWord 

Represents the unsigned int C++ fundamental type. Its equivalent in C# is uint.

ftSignedQuadWord 

Represents the signed long long C++ fundamental type. Its equivalent in C# is long.

ftUnsignedQuadWord 

Represents the unsigned long long C++ fundamental type. Its equivalent in C# is ulong.

ftFloat 

Represents the float C++ fundamental type. Its equivalent in C# is float.

ftDouble 

Represents the double C++ fundamental type. Its equivalent in C# is double.

ftLongDouble 

Represents the long double C++ fundamental type. Its equivalent in C# is double.

ftVoid 

Represents the void C++ fundamental type. Its equivalent in C# is void.

ftAnsiChar 

Represents the char C++ fundamental type. Its equivalents in C# are char and sbyte.
Take into account that the C++ compiler default directive is to interpret char variables as signed char variables, but this can be changed with a compilation flag.

ftWideChar 

Represents the short C++ fundamental type. Its equivalents in C# are char and ushort.
Take into account that the C++ compiler default directive is to interpret short variables as signed short variables, but this can be changed with a compilation flag.

enum eNktErrorCodes

Represents Deviare library error codes.

Enumerator
errCannotLoadDatabase 

Occurs when when the Deviare database cannot be loaded.

errOnlyOneInstance 

Occurs when NktSpyMgr was already running and another instance is trying to be initialized. Only one instance of Deviare manager is allowed per-process.

errProtocolVersionMismatch 

Occurs when communication protocol between agent and manager differ.

errInvalidTransportData 

Occurs when invalid data was transmitted between Deviare agent and manager.

errNotFound 

Occurs when a file, process or referenced handle was not found.

errArithmeticOverflow 

Occurs when arithmetic overflow occurs.

errAlreadyExists 

Occurs when a file, process, handle or object already exists.

errAlreadyInitialized 

Occurs when a NktSpyMgr instance was already initialized.

errCancelled 

Occurs when an asynchronous operation was cancelled.

errExceptionRaised 

Occurs when an internal exception was raised.

errHookIsInactive 

Occurs when a hook is inactive.

errPartialCopy 

Occurs due to unfinished copy operation in ansynchronous or overlapped mode.

errFail 

Occurs when a general failure is triggered.

errOutOfMemory 

Occurs when memory is exhausted.

errNotImpl 

Occurs to inform that a function is not implemented in the interface.

errInvalidArg 

Occurs for invalid or out of range arguments.

errPointer 

Occurs when an invalid or null pointer was referenced.

enum eNktHookFlags

Represents INktHook properties.

Enumerator
flgAutoHookChildProcess 

AutoHookChildProcess flag.
If this flag is set, processes created by the attached processes will also be attached.

flgRestrictAutoHookToSameExecutable 

RestrictAutoHookToSameExecutable flag. This flag can only be used in combination with the AutoHookChildProcess flag.
If this flag is set, child processes will be auto-attached only if they have the same name as their parent.

flgAutoHookActive 

AutoHookActive flag.
If this flag is set, attached processes will be automatically hooked without the need of calling INktHook::Hook.

flgAsyncCallbacks 

AsyncCallbacks flag.
If this flag is set, hooked function calls will be attended, but the caller process will not pause its execution until returning from the OnFunctionCalled event handler. In other words, if this flag is set, there's no guarantee on what the hooked process context will be when the handler is called (i.e. inspecting the caller process memory in an asynchronous handler is likely to lead to inconsistencies).

flgOnlyPreCall 

OnlyPreCall flag.
If this flag is set, Deviare will trigger the OnFunctionCalled event only before a hooked function is called. /// Also, custom handlers or plugins will only receive the OnFunctionCalled event only before a hooked function is called.

flgOnlyPostCall 

OnlyPostCall flag. If this flag is set, Deviare will trigger the OnFunctionCalled event only after a hooked function is called. Also, custom handlers or plugins will only receive the OnFunctionCalled event only after a hooked function is called.

flgDontCheckAddress 

DontCheckAddress flag.
If this flag is set, when creating an INktHook for a specific address will not be submitted to a memory address validity check.

flgDontCallIfLoaderLocked 

DontCallIfLoaderLocked flag.
If this flag is set, the OnFunctionCalled event will not be triggered while the DLL Loader lock is taken.
NOTE: Events filtered by this flag will not be scheduled to be triggered when the DLL Loader lock is released.

flgDontCallCustomHandlersOnLdrLock 

DontCallCustomHandlersOnLdrLock flag.
If this flag is set, custom handlers or plugins will not be called while the DLL Loader lock is taken.
NOTE: Calls filtered by this flag will not be scheduled to be triggered when the DLL Loader lock is released.

flgOnly32Bits 

Only32Bits flag.
If this flag is set, only 32-bit processes are hooked.

flgOnly64Bits 

Only64Bits flag.
If this flag is set, only 64-bit processes are hooked.

flgAddressIsOffset 

AddressIsOffset flag.
The specified address is an offset inside the containing module.

flgInvalidateCache 

InvalidateCache flag.
Invalidates the processor cache

flgDontSkipJumps 

DontSkipJumps flag.
Don't skip initial JMP opcodes that may be found on function being hooked

flgDisableStackWalk 

DisableStackWalk flag.
Don't retrieve stack information

enum eNktHookState

Represents hook states for a specific process.

Enumerator
stInactive 

Inactive state.
Indicates that the hook was not activated for the specified process.

stActivating 

Activating state.
Indicates that the hook is being activated.

stActive 

Active state.
Indicates that the hook is active for the specified process and intercepting function calls.

stDisabled 

Disabled state.
Indicates that a hook is disabled for the specified process.

stRemoved 

Removed state.
Indicates that the hook is not attached to the specified process.

stNotAvailable 

NotAvailable state.
Indicates that the hook is attached to the specified process, but the function or address is temporarily unavailable (i.e. the process did not load the hook's target dll yet).

stNotFound 

NotFound state.
Indicates that the specified hook does not exists.

stError 

Error state.
Indicates that an error occurred while instantiating the hook.

enum eNktProtection

Represents memory page protection properties.
For detailed information on memory management, visit this link.

Enumerator
protExecute 

Execute flag.
This flag is set if executing code from this page is allowed.

protRead 

Read flag.
This flag is set if reading from this page is allowed.

protWrite 

Write flag.
This flag is set if writing to this page is allowed.

protIsWriteCopy 

WriteCopy flag.
This flag is set if the page is marked as copy on write.

protGuard 

Guard flag.
This flag is set if the page is marked as guard.

protNoCache 

NoCache flag.
This flag is set if the page is marked as not cacheable.

protWriteCombine 

WriteCombine flag.
This flag is set if the page is marked as write-combine.

enum eNktSearchMode

Represents search modes when looking for modules and exports by memory address.

Enumerator
smExactMatch 

ExactMatch mode.
Matches modules or exports whose initial memory position equals the specified memory address.

smFindContaining 

FindContaining mode.
Matches the module or export to which the specified memory address belongs.

smGetNearest 

GetNearest match mode.
Same as the FindContaining mode, but extending the module and export ending bounds to the beginning of the next module or export.
